keep proportions of the non-bkg classes in training

This improved the APs on H1 cell type. When classes are balanced, it
fools the model to think there is an equal proportion of each class,
which makes it "over-predict" the under-represented class. This may
decrease the AP of the under-represented class.

Swap LeakyReLU with ReLU to fix odd model outputs

LeakyReLU may have caused model blow-ups to produce all NaNs if the
learning rate was set to be somewhat large (like 0.01). The problem
seemed to disappear after swapping it with ReLU.
